race.description: Guyra Bowling Club Country Boosted Class 1 Handicap
race.comment: Good little contest with plenty of chances. CHICA DEL MAR (3) showed a stack of potential in her first campaign and indicated she was near her best when closing strongly for a slashing second over 1300m at Scone. Gets the right run today and can break through for a well-deserved win. SOULS COMPANION (2) broke through for his maiden win at start two with a fast-finishing performance over 1400m at Moree. Stable apprentice goes on and look for him late. SMILING AMOS (1) tough old gelding who deserves a change of luck for the new yard. Shouldered the 60kg when a gallant on speed fourth over 1300m at Moree second-up. Fitter now and sure to be thereabouts. STOLEN SHOW (11) winkers go on after jumping in trip for a disappointing eighth over 1400m at Tamworth on November 4. Senior rider goes back on today and must be kept safe. TOURTEL (7) good type starting to put it all together. Strong through the line when shedding his maiden tag at start four. Keep safe.
